[Correlation lemma]
Let $(X,R,\mu)$ be an ergodic pmp cber and $(\pi,H)$ an orthogonal representation. Suppose there exist $\delta > 0$, a non-null Borel subset $A \subseteq X$, and a normalised field $\xi$ such that for every $(y,x) \in R|_A$, \begin{equation}\label{eq:prelim1}
\langle \pi(y,x) \xi(x) , \xi(y) \rangle \geq \delta.
\end{equation}
Then $(\pi,H)$ has non-trivial invariant fields.

